{"TopicId":209972,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"What is the Equation for increasing Periapsis at Apoapsis ?","CreatedByName":"5kinflute","CreatedById":223125,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-10-02T08:18:56Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"5kinflute","CreatedById":223125,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-10-02T08:18:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood morning,\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nI have a problem which I can\u0027t comprehend. I use the Trajectory Formula / Conic Section Equation of an orbit and I graphed it from\u003Cstrong\u003E 0 \u0026lt; \u0398 \u0026lt; 2\u03C0 \u003C/strong\u003Eand with it, when I increase my\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003Evelocity\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0, my apoapsis increases as shown in the image:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022image.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002249.59\u0022 height=\u0022122\u0022 width=\u0022246\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/NmZ1MyG/image.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen I set my true anomaly to 180 degrees (apoapsis), and increase velocity... my periapsis doesn\u0027t increase in height but apoapsis continues to increase.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nMy desired behavior is:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022image.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002253.57\u0022 height=\u0022105\u0022 width=\u0022196\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/tHYh3mG/image.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nIn KSP, the periapsis angle and apoapsis angles both shifts to the correct values, but how is this done mathematically?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nThanks,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n5kinflute\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-10-02T08:22:39Z\u0022 title=\u002210/02/2022 08:22  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 2, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by 5kinflute\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Ewrong pictures\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Shpaget","CreatedById":45577,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-10-02T13:37:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVis viva equation may be what you\u0027re looking for.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vis-viva_equation\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vis-viva_equation\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tomf","CreatedById":57809,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-10-02T20:07:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo elaborate I would get the sma of the current orbit and use vis Viva to get my velocity at pe, then I would get the sma of the desired orbit and calculate the required velocity at pe\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"5kinflute","CreatedById":223125,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-10-03T05:48:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthanks guys, I also realized this is possible because of\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003Especific mechanical energy\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0which is constant\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022energy.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002233.33\u0022 height=\u0022120\u0022 width=\u0022360\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/gF40L3N/energy.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003Eenergy (constant) = kinetic energy \u002B potential\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003Eim really new to orbital mechanics so this went over my head\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-10-03T05:49:54Z\u0022 title=\u002210/03/2022 05:49  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 3, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by 5kinflute\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dinlink","CreatedById":222278,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-10-10T07:15:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have done a detailed walkthrough of an example calculation on this thread:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022222278\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1820062943\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/209989-specific-calculations/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=4182086\u0026amp;embedComment=4182086\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022 style=\u0022height:261px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHole you find it useful!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-10-10T07:39:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224181620\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209972\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221664776109\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022223125\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225kinflute\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 10/3/2022 at 8:48 AM, 5kinflute said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbecause of\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003Especific mechanical energy\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Angular_momentum#Conservation_of_angular_momentum\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Eangular momentum is also constant\u003C/a\u003E. It\u0027s another part of because.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}